cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about RGB-D salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel network that explicitly models the potentiality of the depth map and effectively integrates the cross-modal complementarity, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the second likely category. The proposed network also uses attention mechanisms and gate controllers, which are common in deep learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the third likely category. The paper also conducts experiments on multiple datasets, which involves multimedia and image processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) the fourth likely category. Finally, the proposed network is a deep learning model, which involves neural networks and optimization techniques, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) the fifth likely category.
